> system
You are a pragmatic coding assistant that prefers clean minimalist code.

> user
Setup a basic React app with tailwind v4 support using the Bun cli.

Setup the project at `./react-bun-example`



> assistant
Run this script from the directory where you want `./react-bun-example` created:

<RUNNABLE_SCRIPT script-name="setup-react-bun-tailwind-v4" target-shell-type="bash">
```bash
set -euo pipefail

# Ensure Bun is available
command -v bun >/dev/null 2>&1 || {
  echo "Bun is not installed or not in PATH."
  echo "Install it from: https://bun.sh"
  exit 1
}

# Avoid accidentally overwriting existing work
if [ -e "./react-bun-example" ]; then
  echo "./react-bun-example already exists. Remove it or choose another directory."
  exit 1
fi

# Create a basic React app using Vite through the Bun CLI
bun create vite ./react-bun-example --template react

cd ./react-bun-example

# Install dependencies
bun install

# Add Tailwind CSS v4 and the official Vite plugin
bun add -d tailwindcss @tailwindcss/vite

# Configure Vite to use React and Tailwind v4
cat > vite.config.js <<'EOF'
import { defineConfig } from 'vite'
import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react'
import tailwindcss from '@tailwindcss/vite'

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react(), tailwindcss()],
})
EOF

# Replace the default CSS with Tailwind v4 import
cat > src/index.css <<'EOF'
@import "tailwindcss";
EOF

# Create a minimal Tailwind-styled React app
cat > src/App.jsx <<'EOF'
function App() {
  return (
    <main className="min-h-screen bg-zinc-950 text-white flex items-center justify-center p-6">
      <section className="max-w-xl text-center space-y-6">
        <div className="inline-flex rounded-full bg-cyan-500/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-cyan-300 ring-1 ring-cyan-500/20">
          React + Bun + Tailwind CSS v4
        </div>

        <h1 className="text-4xl sm:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight">
          Hello from Bun
        </h1>

        <p className="text-zinc-400 text-lg">
          A minimal React app powered by Vite, Bun, and Tailwind CSS v4.
        </p>

        <a
          href="https://tailwindcss.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
          className="inline-flex rounded-lg bg-white px-5 py-3 font-medium text-zinc-950 hover:bg-zinc-200 transition"
        \>
          Tailwind Docs
        </a>
      </section>
    </main>
  )
}

export default App
EOF

echo ""
echo "Done."
echo "Next steps:"
echo "  cd react-bun-example"
echo "  bun dev"
```
</RUNNABLE_SCRIPT>

Then start the app:

```bash
cd react-bun-example
bun dev
```


